ly Law (TV series)|Family Law]]''\n| 2000\n| Camille Weller\n| 1 episode\n|-\n| ''[[Queen of Swords (TV series)|Queen of Swords]]''\n| 2000\n| Mary Rose\n| 1 episode [[The Witness (Queen of Swords)|\"The Witness\"]]\n|-\n| ''[[Murder at the Cannes Film Festival]]''\n| 2000\n| Thada Pryce\n| Television movie\n|-\n| ''[[Two Guys, a Girl and a Pizza Place]]''\n| 2001\n| Susan Bergen\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| ''[[Lucky (TV series)|Lucky]]''\n| 2003\n| Joan\n| 1 episode\n|-\n| ''[[Still Standing (TV series)|Still Standing]]''\n| 2005\n| Mrs. Rose Grundy\n| 1 episode\n|-\n| ''[[7th Heaven (TV series)|7th Heaven]]''\n| 2003\u201305\n| Mrs. Kinkirk\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| ''Crusader''\n| 2005\n| Nicola Markham\n| Television movie\n|-\n| ''[[Fashion House]]''\n| 2006\n| Maria Gianni\n| 40 episodes\n|-\n| ''The Hunt for the I-5 Killer''\n| 2011\n| Seaver\n| Television movie\n|-\n| ''[[Chuck (TV series)|Chuck]]''\n| 2012\n| Herself\n| Season 5, Episode 10 \"Chuck Versus Bo\"\n|-\n| ''[[CSI: Miami]]''\n| 2012\n| Joanna Toring\n| Season 10, Episode 14\n|-\n| ''[[Sharknado 3: Oh Hell No!]]''\n| 2015\n| May Wexler\n| Television movie\n|-\n| ''[[The Last Sharknado: It's About Time]]''\n| 2018\n| May Wexler\n| Television movie\n|}\n\n== Production credits ==\n\n=== Film ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n| '''Film'''\n| '''Genre'''\n| '''Year'''\n| '''Role'''\n| '''Notes'''\n|-\n| ''[[Love You (film)|Love You]]''\n| Porn\n| 1979\n| Producer\n| John Derek directed the film.{{cn|date=November 2018}}\n|-\n| ''[[Ghosts Can't Do It]]''\n| Romantic Comedy\n| 1989\n| Producer, Actor\n| \n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.angelfire.com/rock2/rockinterviews/boderek.html Interview with Bo Derek]\n* {{IMDb name|0000137}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Derek, Bo}}\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Long Beach, California]]\n[