ending.com/|title=Cyberpunk Bartender Action VA-11 HALL-A|website=waifubartending.com|language=en|access-date=2017-07-24}}</ref>\n* ''[[Observer (video game)|Observer]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[Ruiner (video game)|Ruiner]]'' (2017)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2017/09/27/ruiner-tacoma-cyberpunk-sci-fi-blade-runner-philosophy-video-games/|title=The evolution of video-game cyberpunk: 'Ruiner' and 'Tacoma'|author=|date=|website=Engadget|access-date=28 April 2019}}</ref>\n* ''[[The Red Strings Club]]'' (2018)<ref>{{cite web|title=Devolver Digital, The Red Strings Club|url=https://www.devolverdigital.com/games/view/the-red-strings-club|accessdate= 2018-01-15}}</ref>\n* ''[[Astral Chain]]'' (2019)<ref>{{cite web|title=Astral Chain's director talks about Nier, the police, and cyberpunk|website=Polygon|url=https://www.polygon.com/interviews/2019/6/17/18682365/astral-chain-nintendo-switch-e3-2019-platinumgames-interview-nier-automata|accessdate= 2019-06-27|date=2019-06-17}}</ref>\n* ''[[Cyberpunk 2077]]'' (2020)\n* ''[[The Last Night (video game)|The Last Night]]'' (TBA)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://oddtales.net/|title=The Last Night official website - created by Odd Tales|website=oddtales.net|access-date=2017-07-16}}</ref>\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Tabletop Games===\n* The ''[[Cyberpunk 2020|Cyberpunk]]'' RPG (1988)\n* ''[[Shadowrun]]'' (1989)\n* ''[[GURPS Cyberpunk]]'' (1990)<ref>{{cite web|title=GURPS Cyberpunk|url=http://www.sjgames.com/gurps/books/cyberpunk/|accessdate= 2009-02-04}}</ref>\n* ''[[Corporation (role playing game)|Corporation]]'' (2009) <ref>{{cite web|title=Corporation RPG|url=http://www.corpgame.com|accessdate=2015-05-06 }}</ref>\n* ''[[The Sprawl]]'' (2016)\n* ''[[Interface Zero 3.0]]'' (2019)\n\n==Related nonfiction==\n* ''[[A Cyborg Manifesto]]'' (1991), by [[Donna Haraway]]\n* ''[[Storming the Reality Studio]]: A Casebook of Cyberpunk & Postmodern Science Fiction'' (1992), edited by [[Larry McCaffery]] (contains both fiction and nonfiction)<ref name=\