 (novel)|Glasshouse]]'' (2006)<ref>{{cite web|title=Book review: Glasshouse by Charles Stross|url=http://ttapress.com/223/book-review-glasshouse-by-charles-stross/|accessdate= 2009-02-04}}</ref>\n* ''[[Daemon (technothriller series)|Daemon]]'' (2006\u20132010) by [[Daniel Suarez (author)|Daniel Suarez]]\n* ''[[The Mirrored Heavens]]'' (2008) by [[David J. Williams]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Mirrored Heavens: Taking cyberpunk to the stratosphere | url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/books/2008071097_mirrored25.html | date=2008-07-25|accessdate= 2009-09-19 | work=The Seattle Times | first=Nisi | last=Shawl}}\n</ref>\n* ''[[Ready Player One]]'' (2011) by [[Ernest Cline]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tor.com/2016/06/09/evolution-of-virtual-realities-cyberpunk-real-world/|title=The Evolution of Virtual Realities in Cyberpunk and the Real World|last=Zutter|first=Natalie|date=June 9, 2016|website=Tor.com|access-date=December 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.davidwrick.com/2013/07/24/ernest-clines-ready-player-one/|title=Ernest Cline's READY PLAYER ONE is 80s Cyberpunk Bliss|last=Rick|first=David|date=July 24, 2013|website=Davidwrick.com|access-date=December 15, 2018}}</ref>\n* ''[[Bleeding Edge]]'' (2013) by [[Thomas Pynchon]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Pynchon's Deep Web|date=September 10, 2013 |url=http://lareviewofbooks.org/review/pynchons-deep-web/}}</ref>\n* ''[[Blackstar (novel)|Blackstar]]'' (2013\u20132015) by [[Josh Viola]]\n* ''[[Cash Crash Jubilee]]'' (2015)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/978-1-940456-27-0|title=Fiction Book Review: Cash Crash Jubilee by Eli K.P. William. Skyhorse/Talos,ISBN 978-1-940456-27-0|last=|first=|date=|work=PublishersWeekly.com|access-date=2018-05-01|language=en}}</ref> by Eli K.P. William\n** ''[[The Naked World]]'' (2017)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/culture/2017/12/02/books/book-reviews/eli-k-p-williams-dystopian-naked-world-not-tale-technophobes/#.WiNGgktx0U8|title=Eli K. P. William's dystopian 'The Naked World' is not a tale for technophobes {{!}} The Japan Times|work=The Japan Times|access-date=2018-05-01|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n===Short stories, anthologies, and single-author collections===\n* ''[[Cyberpunk (novel)|Cyberpunk]]'' (1983) by [[Bruce Bethke]]\n* ''[[Burning Chrome (short story collection)|Burning Chrome]]'' (1986) by [[William Gibson]]\n* ''[[Mirrorshades|Mirrorshades: The Cyberpunk Anthology]]'' (1986) edited by [[Bruce Sterling]]<ref name=mason/><ref>{{cite book|title= Canadian Science Fiction and Fantasy By David Ketterer|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=zvARp4yM1sUC&pg=PA141&dq=Cyberpunk+high-tech+low-life|accessdate= 2009-02-04|publisher= Indiana University Press|isbn= 978-0-253-33122-9|author1= Ketterer, David|year= 1992}}</ref>\n* ''[[Patterns]]'' (1989) by Pat Cadigan\n* ''[[Crystal Express]]'' (1989) by [[Bruce Sterling]]<ref name=mason/>\n* ''[[Storming the Reality Studio]]: A Casebook of Cyberpunk & Postmodern Science Fiction'' (1992) edited by [[Larry McCaffery]] (contains both fiction and nonfiction)<ref name=\"streettech.com\">{{cite web|title=Storming the Reality Studio: A Casebook of Cyberpunk and Postmodern Science Fiction|url=http://www.streettech.com/bcp/BCPgraf/Manifestos/storming.htm|accessdate= 2010-11-15}}</ref>\n* ''[[Hackers (short stories)|Hackers]]'' (1996) by Jack Dann & Gardner Dozois\n\n===Graphic novels and comics===\n* ''[[Judge Dredd]]'' (1977\u2013) by [[John Wagner]] and [[Carlos Ezquerra]]\n* ''[[The Incal]]'' (1981\u20131989) by [[Alejandro Jodorowsky]]\n* ''[[Akira (manga)|Akira]]'' (1982\u20131990) by [[Katsuhiro \u014ctomo]]<ref name=\"asimovs.com\">{{cite web|title=Thought Experiments: Cyberpunk is Alive and Well and Living in - Where Else?- Japan|url=http://www.asimovs.com/_issue_0602/Thougthexperiments.shtml|accessdate= 2009-02-04}}</ref>\n* ''[[Black Magic (manga)|Black Magic]]'' (1983) by [[Masamune Shirow]]\n* ''[[Ronin (DC Comics)|Ronin]]'' (1983\u20131984) by [[Frank Miller (comics)|Frank Miller]]\n* ''[[Appleseed (manga)|Appleseed]]'' (1985\u20131989) by [[Masamune Shirow]]\n* ''[[Dominion (manga)|Dominion]]'' (1986) by [[Masamune Shirow]]\n* ''[[Ghost in the Shell (manga)|Ghost in the Shell]]'' (1989\u20131991) by [[Masamune Shirow]]\n* ''[[Neuromancer#Graphic novel|Neuromancer]]'' (1989) by Tom de Haven and [[Bruce Jensen]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Neuromancer Graphic Novel|url=http://www.antonraubenweiss.com/gibson/gallery/neuromancer-graphicnovel/gn00.html|accessdate= 2009-02-04}}</ref>\n* ''[[Battle Angel Alita]]'' (1990\u20131995) by [[Yukito Kishiro]]<ref name=\"asimovs.com\"/>\n* ''[[Barb Wire]]'' (1994\u20131995) by [[Chris Warner (comics)|Chris Warner]]\n* ''[[Transmetropolitan]]'' (1997\u20132002) by [[Warren Ellis]]<ref>{{cite news|title=My Science Fiction Life|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/dna/mysciencefictionlife/A17526396|accessdate= 2009-02-04}}</ref>\n* ''[[Eden: It's an Endless World!]]'' (1998\u20132008) by [[Hiroki Endo]]\n* ''[[Blame!]]'' (1998) by [[Tsutomu Nihei]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Cyberpunk World of Tsutomu Nihei|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/index.asp?layout=talkBackCommentsFull&articleid=CA6347389&talk_back_header_id=6347389|accessdate= 2009-02-04|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080225214042/http://www.publishersweekly.com/index.asp?layout=talkbackCommentsFull&talk_back_header_id=6347389&articleid=CA6347389|archivedate=25 February 2008}}</ref>\n** ''[[NOiSE]]'' (2001) \u2013 prequel to ''Blame!''\n** ''[[Biomega (manga)|Biomega]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[Singularity 7]]'' (2004) by [[Ben Templesmith]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Building an Artistic Temple|url=http://www.brokenfrontier.com/lowdown/details.php?id=314|accessdate= 2009-02-05|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061112144100/http://www.brokenfrontier.com/lowdown/details.php?id=314 |archivedate=November 12, 2006 }}</ref>\n* ''[[The Surrogates]]'' (2005) by [[Robert Venditti]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Surrogates: From Page to Screen|url=h