06 film)|Renaissance]]'' (2006)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.7mpictures.com/inside/reviews/dvdblitz6_review.htm#renaissancedvd |title=DVD Review Blitz by Kevin Carr |publisher=7M Pictures |accessdate=2009-02-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081121223853/http://www.7mpictures.com/inside/reviews/dvdblitz6_review.htm#renaissancedvd |archive-date=2008-11-21 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* ''[[Denn\u014d Coil]]'' (2007)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://abandonedfactory.wordpress.com/2012/03/19/dennou-coil-final-thoughts-people-are-connected-through-narrow-paths/ |title=Denn\u014d Coil |accessdate=2013-08-12}}</ref>\n* ''[[Vexille]]'' (2007)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dvdtalk.com/reviews/33360/vexille/ |title=Vexille : DVD Talk Review of the DVD Video |publisher=Dvdtalk.com |accessdate=2009-06-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.birminghampost.net/life-leisure-birmingham-guide/birmingham-culture/film-news/2008/06/11/incredible-hulk-finds-strength-in-depth-65233-21059801/ |title=Life & Leisure - Birmingham Culture - Film - Incredible Hulk finds strength in depth |newspaper=Birmingham Post |date=2008-06-11 |accessdate=2009-06-13}}</ref>\n* ''[[Technotise: Edit & I]]'' (2009, Serbia)<ref name=\"Technotise: Edit & I 1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fantasiafestival.com/2010/en/films/film_detail.php?id=92|title=Technotise: Edit & I\n|publisher=Fantasia International Film Festival 2010|first=Rupert|last=Bottenberg|date=July 11, 2010|accessdate=2007-07-20}}</ref>\n* ''[[Real Drive]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Mardock Scramble]]'' (2010)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2010-11-06/1st-mardock-scramble-cyberpunk-film-trailer-streamed |title=1st Mardock Scramble Cyberpunk Film's Trailer Streamed |work=Anime News Network |accessdate=2012-05-26}}</ref>\n* ''[[Accel World]]'' (2012\u20132016)\n* ''[[Psycho-Pass]]'' (2012)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/psycho-pass/episodes-1 |title=Psycho-Pass Episodes 1-11 Streaming |work=Anime New